<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="360" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="83.[2060,2655,720,1146]" pageId="83" pageNumber="360">
Neotomaferruginea was initially described as a distinct species, and then it was relegat- ed to a subspecies of N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baird" authorityYear="1855" box="[2428,2548,878,911]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="83" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicana">mexicana</taxonomicName>
, where it remained until it was resurrected to full species status. During recent taxonomic revision, several subspecies of N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baird" authorityYear="1855" box="[2536,2654,1004,1029]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="83" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicana">mexicana</taxonomicName>
were reevaluated and assigned to N. 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="83" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferruginea">ferruginea</taxonomicName>
, resulting in four subspecies being affiliated with N. 
<taxonomicName box="[2270,2406,1113,1146]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="83" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferruginea">ferruginea</taxonomicName>
. It is unclearif N.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="83.[1448,2657,1154,2251]" box="[1451,2515,1154,1187]" pageId="83" pageNumber="360">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baird" authorityYear="1855" box="[1451,1570,1154,1187]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="83" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicana">mexicana</taxonomicName>
solitaria is a subspecies of N. 
<taxonomicName box="[1971,2107,1154,1187]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="83" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferruginea">ferruginea</taxonomicName>
. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
